# Parallel agent collision safety

When unexpected edits or files appear, assume parallel work may be happening.

- Before editing, deleting, staging, or committing, check whether another agent
  may be working in the same area.
- Strong signals include unexpected modified or untracked files, new
  orchestrator outputs, or user context that suggests multiple agents are
  active.
- If overlap is plausible, do not guess file ownership.
- Prefer a safe strategy:
  - narrow work to non-overlapping files
  - re-read the affected files and current git status before editing
  - stage only files you changed yourself
  - ask the user before touching ambiguous changes
- Never overwrite, delete, or commit another agent's changes without explicit
  confirmation.
- If parallel work is intentional, think through a collision-avoidance plan
  before continuing mechanically.
